Body:
Located in one of the cities fastest growing suburbs, this incredible home tucked away behind the hedge and fence has been completely transformed! This is a property you will be proud to call your home, having undergone a recent renovation with the addition of an extra lounge and large deck!

Outside, this 787m2 section has so much to offer. North facing, fully fenced/secure and incredibly sheltered this property provides a fantastic opportunity for growing families. A large brand-new deck flows to your very own BBQ/gazebo area – perfect for summer barbeques and outdoor entertaining. Follow the garden path just past the veggie garden and you will find your very own teenage retreat or home office! Although this space is unconsented, is has been transformed into a fabulous area with a bedroom, kitchenette and bathroom.

This home offers:

· Spacious Master Bedroom with ensuite and private deck

· Two additional double bedrooms

· A kitchen which was designed with the Entertainer in mind! This is your hub of the home, with great bench space and a 900mm gas hob – fellow chefs will be impressed!

· Two living zones meaning there’s space for everyone in this family home

· All day sun and superb indoor/outdoor flow

Within walking distance to the beach, South Brighton Surf Club, popular Dune café, and great proximity to Taiora QEII, He Puna Taimoana Hot Pools, New Brighton Pier. Handy to local amenities including supermarkets and public transport and fantastic school zoning.

My owners have flights booked and bags packed! This home will sell on or before auction day so don’t delay - Enjoy a seaside lifestyle that you will love coming home to. Call Fiona Williams today.

Title: * Under Offer * Room To Spread Out

Attributes.Name: location
Attributes.Value: 17 Tivoli Place, Bishopdale, Christchurch City, Canterbury

Body:
Negotiable Over $645,000

** Multiple Offers made, if you're thinking of selling nearby, I have buyers actively looking who missed out ** 


If you're looking for a spacious home, in a quiet cul de sac (off another cul de sac) I encourage you to come and have a look at this property.

Built in 1997, this 250m2 (approx.) home features ample proportions throughout.

4 Spacious double bedrooms, the master with walk in robe and ensuite.

Two hot water cylinders with the ensuite enjoying an exclusive one.

Double glazed throughout, with a floor mounted heat pump in the open plan living, and a second heat pump in the hallway servicing the bedroom end of the home.

Generous open plan living with kitchen, dining and lounge, with a dual access additional lounge adjacent.

Both living rooms have ranch sliders to the patio in the back yard.

The carpet was replaced 2 years ago, as well as a full internal repaint in neutral shades. Vinyl was replaced at the same time.

Plenty of storage throughout with two double wardrobes in the hallway, as well as an additional cupboard at the end of the hall, with a double wardrobe in the separate laundry and supersized wardrobes in the bedrooms.

Double internal garage with auto door, with a dedicated pad out front for your caravan or boat. A caravan plug is a bonus.

With the dry summer we currently have, you will appreciate that the lawns and gardens have irrigation.

This 1 owner from new, spacious family home is beautifully presented inside and out! Interest is bound to be high so come along to the first open home or call me to view.

Zoned TC2, GV $700,000

#Redwood #Harewood #Northwood #Glasnevin #Regents Park #Casebrook
